org.apache.river.test.spec.url.file.integrity

Class ProvidesIntegrity

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.qa.harness.QATestEnvironment
      • org.apache.river.test.spec.url.util.AbstractProvidesIntegrity
        • org.apache.river.test.spec.url.file.integrity.ProvidesIntegrity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Test, TestEnvironment

    public class ProvidesIntegrity
extends AbstractProvidesIntegrity
    
 Purpose:
   This test verifies the behavior of the
   FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method.
   FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
   should return:
     true   if the specified URL uses the "file" protocol and
            the host is null, empty, "~", or "localhost";
     false  otherwise.
   The method throws:
     NullPointerException - if the URL is null

 Test Cases:
   This test invokes
   FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
   with different URL objects.
   The cases:
     - testcase1: (FILE URL object)
         protocol of URL: tc1_prot
         host     of URL: tc1_host
         file     of URL: tc1_file
       It's expected that
       FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
       returns tc1_expected.
     - testcase2: (FILE URL object)
         protocol of URL: tc2_prot
         host     of URL: tc2_host
         file     of URL: tc2_file
       It's expected that
       FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
       returns tc2_expected.
     - testcase3: (FILE URL object)
         protocol of URL: tc3_prot
         host     of URL: tc3_host
         file     of URL: tc3_file
       It's expected that
       FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
       returns tc3_expected.
     - testcase4: (FILE URL object)
         protocol of URL: tc4_prot
         host     of URL: tc4_host
         file     of URL: tc4_file
       It's expected that
       FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
       returns tc4_expected.
     - testcase5: (FILE URL object)
         protocol of URL: tc5_prot
         host     of URL: tc5_host
         file     of URL: tc5_file
       It's expected that
       FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
       returns tc5_expected.
     - testcase6: (HTTPMD URL object)
         protocol of URL: tc6_prot
         host     of URL: tc6_host
         file     of URL: tc6_file
       It's expected that
       FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
       returns tc6_expected.
     - testcase7: (HTTPS URL object)
         protocol of URL: tc7_prot
         host     of URL: tc7_host
         file     of URL: tc7_file
       It's expected that
       FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
       returns tc7_expected.
     - testcase8: (HTTP URL object)
         protocol of URL: tc8_prot
         host     of URL: tc8_host
         file     of URL: tc8_file
       It's expected that
       FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
       returns tc8_expected.
     - testcase9: (URL object = null)
         protocol of URL: tc9_prot
         host     of URL: tc9_host
         file     of URL: tc9_file
       It's expected that
       FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL) method
       throws tc9_expected.

 Infrastructure:
     - AbstractProvidesIntegrity
         abstract class that is extended by ProvidesIntegrity class
     - AbstractProvidesIntegrity.TestItem
         auxiliary class that describes a Test Case
     - ProvidesIntegrity
         performs actions

 Actions:
   Jini Harness does the following before running the test:
     - setting java.protocol.handler.pkgs property to
       net.jini.url to enable HTTPMD urls creating
       (Handler is used as HTTPMD Protocol
       handler).
   Test performs the following steps:
     - creating FileIntegrityVerifier object,
     - in each Test Case the test does the following:
       1) constructing a
          AbstractProvidesIntegrity.TestItem
          object,
       2) invoking
          FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL)
          method for the specified URL object,
       3) comparing
          FileIntegrityVerifier.providesIntegrity(URL)
          result (true, false or exception) with the expected result from
          the
          AbstractProvidesIntegrity.TestItem
          object.
